561
00:50:33,025 --> 00:50:34,158
Which, of course,

562
00:50:34,159 --> 00:50:37,462
is how Pat and I came
to know each other.

563
00:50:41,706 --> 00:50:43,537
What phobia was that?

564
00:50:43,538 --> 00:50:44,538
<i>Patrick.</i>

565
00:50:45,772 --> 00:50:46,772
<i>Patrick.</i>

566
00:50:48,372 --> 00:50:49,540
<i>Let's you and me take a walk.</i>

567
00:50:50,644 --> 00:50:51,644
Come on.

568
00:50:55,052 --> 00:50:56,652
You know, long before
we built this yard,

569
00:50:57,720 --> 00:50:59,414
this whole forest

570
00:50:59,415 --> 00:51:01,387
was basically one
big copper mine.

571
00:51:03,754 --> 00:51:05,674
Kicked out half the product
for the entire state,

572
00:51:06,964 --> 00:51:08,724
before they finally
dug the sucker dry.

573
00:51:11,763 --> 00:51:13,803
This was how you got down
to the main entry shaft...

574
00:51:15,268 --> 00:51:17,304
back when it was owned
by the mining company.

575
00:51:18,435 --> 00:51:19,635
Who owns it now?

576
00:51:20,806 --> 00:51:21,806
Us?

577
00:51:29,415 --> 00:51:31,351
Now it belongs to Bagman.

578
00:51:34,926 --> 00:51:36,719
- Who's Bagman?
- Shh!

579
00:51:40,591 --> 00:51:42,590
You never know who
might be listenin'.

580
00:51:42,591 --> 00:51:44,594
I told your brother
this story last summer,

581
00:51:44,595 --> 00:51:47,034
just like your granddad
did me when I was your age

582
00:51:47,035 --> 00:51:49,133
and his granddad's
granddad before that.

583
00:51:49,134 --> 00:51:51,437
And all of them
swore it was true.

584
00:51:53,273 --> 00:51:54,605
Just like I'm
swearing to you now.

585
00:51:56,547 --> 00:51:57,608
They say...

586
00:51:58,641 --> 00:52:00,545
he wanders the world each night,

587
00:52:01,311 --> 00:52:02,410
searching for children

588
00:52:02,411 --> 00:52:04,615
to stuff in that
awful bag a' his.

589
00:52:05,782 --> 00:52:07,719
- Not just any children...
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

590
00:52:07,720 --> 00:52:09,557
Let me guess.

591
00:52:09,558 --> 00:52:11,659
He wants the naughty children that
don't listen to their parents or...

592
00:52:11,660 --> 00:52:13,558
Wrong, Patty.

593
00:52:14,831 --> 00:52:16,297
It's the good kids he wants.

594
00:52:17,330 --> 00:52:19,630
The shiny ones and the dreamers.

595
00:52:21,137 --> 00:52:23,568
Once they catch his
eye, or grab his fancy,

596
00:52:24,502 --> 00:52:26,334
he won't rest until he has them

597
00:52:26,335 --> 00:52:29,076
slung over his bony shoulder.

598
00:52:29,077 --> 00:52:31,477
Screamin' for help
that's never gonna come.

599
00:52:36,350 --> 00:52:37,546
No, you're just
trying to scare me...

600
00:52:37,547 --> 00:52:38,984
Damn right, I'm trying
to scare you, boy.

601
00:52:38,985 --> 00:52:40,219
<i>And scared you better be!</i>

602
00:52:40,220 --> 00:52:41,484
<i>Wander too close,
he'll drag you in</i>

603
00:52:41,485 --> 00:52:43,253
<i>and make pencils
out of your fingers,</i>

604
00:52:43,254 --> 00:52:44,688
and gobble the rest of you down!

605
00:52:47,390 --> 00:52:48,659
Are you with me, boy?

606
00:52:52,503 --> 00:52:53,503
<i>Good.</i>

607
00:52:54,099 --> 00:52:55,171
Bagman?

608
00:53:21,357 --> 00:53:22,693
You drew these?

609
00:53:25,766 --> 00:53:26,766
Yep.

610
00:53:38,711 --> 00:53:40,751
That's what I meant by
a persistent phobia.

611
00:53:41,884 --> 00:53:43,615
Pat's was so intense,

612
00:53:44,648 --> 00:53:46,183
I felt it was
crucial to give him

613
00:53:46,184 --> 00:53:48,584
as much context as possible

614
00:53:48,585 --> 00:53:50,952
for the familial lore
that provoked it.

615
00:53:57,234 --> 00:54:02,268
As you can see, the
so-called Bag or Sackman,

616
00:54:02,269 --> 00:54:05,307
is a figure common to
almost every culture.

617
00:54:06,470 --> 00:54:09,210
Curiously, his methodology,

618
00:54:09,211 --> 00:54:11,742
even the phenomena that
accompany his presence,

619
00:54:12,476 --> 00:54:15,410
are remarkably consistent.

620
00:54:15,411 --> 00:54:17,677
He has the power to paralyze

621
00:54:17,678 --> 00:54:20,516
and incapacitate
parents and adults

622
00:54:20,517 --> 00:54:23,223
leaving their young
ones vulnerable.

623
00:54:23,224 --> 00:54:26,421
And he feeds off the
child's fear and anxiety.

624
00:54:26,422 --> 00:54:30,727
It sustains him, nourishes him.

625
00:54:30,728 --> 00:54:34,928
He can lure children to his
lair with toys or candy...

626
00:54:34,929 --> 00:54:38,403
And when the child is
at their most terrified,

627
00:54:38,404 --> 00:54:41,772
he steals them away
in his sack or bag.

628
00:54:42,839 --> 00:54:44,238
Are you trying to
make us feel stupid?

629
00:54:44,239 --> 00:54:45,741
On the contrary.

630
00:54:45,742 --> 00:54:49,910
I never told Karina about
the Bagman, Barbara,

631
00:54:49,911 --> 00:54:52,582
and it wasn't a dream
that broke into our house.

632
00:54:52,583 --> 00:54:56,155
No, but I'd suggest,
as a coping mechanism,

633
00:54:56,156 --> 00:54:58,726
you're projecting
the supernatural

634
00:54:58,727 --> 00:55:00,422
onto something...

635
00:55:00,423 --> 00:55:03,592
all too painfully real.

636
00:55:03,593 --> 00:55:06,998
And until you deal
with the real stuff

637
00:55:06,999 --> 00:55:08,370
bubbling up for you,

638
00:55:09,233 --> 00:55:10,666
the anger,

639
00:55:10,667 --> 00:55:14,569
the feelings of
vulnerability, and violation,

640
00:55:14,570 --> 00:55:17,008
your panic attacks
and nightmares

641
00:55:17,009 --> 00:55:18,644
will only get worse.

642
00:55:19,311 --> 00:55:20,514
Okay, so,

643
00:55:21,446 --> 00:55:22,813
what do you suggest we do?

644
00:55:27,350 --> 00:55:28,482
I see her.

645
00:55:28,483 --> 00:55:31,426
I'm the zombie.

646
00:55:32,690 --> 00:55:33,787
- Whoa! Hey, guys.
- Okay.

647
00:55:33,788 --> 00:55:35,625
So, he goes down
7:30 at the latest.

648
00:55:35,626 --> 00:55:37,424
- We read two stories...
- Two stories, yeah.

649
00:55:37,425 --> 00:55:38,965
And then we sing <i>Frere Jacques</i>
when he goes in the Pack 'n Play.

650
00:55:38,966 --> 00:55:40,667
Guys, check your phone.

651
00:55:40,668 --> 00:55:42,963
I just texted you the confirmation
number for a room at the Hyatt.

652
00:55:42,964 --> 00:55:44,332
Two blocks from here,
three from the restaurant.

653
00:55:44,333 --> 00:55:45,934
Already paid for.

654
00:55:45,935 --> 00:55:47,706
Dinner's one thing, but
there's no chance in hell

655
00:55:47,707 --> 00:55:49,604
we're sleeping in a different
place than Jakie right now.

656
00:55:49,605 --> 00:55:51,339
Who said anything
about sleeping?

657
00:55:51,340 --> 00:55:53,613
Who said sleeping?

658
00:55:54,878 --> 00:55:56,113
Will you just get
her out of here, Pat?

659
00:55:56,114 --> 00:55:57,713
Who said...

660
00:55:57,714 --> 00:56:00,019
Jakie, listen to
Auntie Anna, okay?

661
00:56:00,020 --> 00:56:01,188
Call any time!

662
00:56:01,189 --> 00:56:03,620
We can be back, five
minutes tops, okay?

663
00:56:03,621 --> 00:56:05,341
Gonna play zombie.

664
00:56:11,267 --> 00:56:12,863
I'm not sure I'm up for this.

665
00:56:15,268 --> 00:56:16,438
Yeah, me neither.

666
00:56:19,103 --> 00:56:23,610
Worst case, we get dinner to
go and eat on Anna's couch.

667
00:56:25,145 --> 00:56:26,710
Yep.

668
00:56:26,711 --> 00:56:28,916
Let's at least try to
make it as far as dessert,

669
00:56:28,917 --> 00:56:29,957
so she can put Jakie down.

670
00:56:37,059 --> 00:56:38,059
So, what's the verdict?

671
00:56:41,965 --> 00:56:42,965
Is your husband nuts?

672
00:56:46,661 --> 00:56:47,898
Completely fricking crackers.

673
00:56:54,138 --> 00:56:57,413
So, what actually happened
with you and Liam at the mine?

674
00:56:59,616 --> 00:57:03,078
Well, I thought I felt someone
cut off a lock of my hair.

675
00:57:05,084 --> 00:57:06,084
I, uh...

676
00:57:07,484 --> 00:57:08,682
I lost my shit

677
00:57:08,683 --> 00:57:11,386
and then we ran home screaming.

678
00:57:11,387 --> 00:57:13,557
A lock of your hair?

679
00:57:13,558 --> 00:57:16,362
Yeah. Bagman
supposedly always snips

680
00:57:16,363 --> 00:57:18,093
one off the kids
that catch his fancy.

681
00:57:19,002 --> 00:57:20,161
That's how it starts.

682
00:57:21,301 --> 00:57:22,301
What the hell for?

683
00:57:23,703 --> 00:57:25,899
So he always knows
where to find you.

684
00:57:25,900 --> 00:57:28,103
No matter where you
try to run or hide.

685
00:57:32,347 --> 00:57:35,110
Your father was something else.

686
00:57:35,111 --> 00:57:38,284
I think in his own way he was
just trying to protect me.

687
00:57:38,285 --> 00:57:39,950
A cautionary tale
to keep me safe.

688
00:57:44,855 --> 00:57:46,457
All I remember was
Mom was furious

689
00:57:46,458 --> 00:57:48,293
'cause every night
I was convinced

690
00:57:48,294 --> 00:57:49,564
he was tapping on my window.

691
00:57:50,528 --> 00:57:52,595
And then one night,

692
00:57:52,596 --> 00:57:54,965
the old man came in and he said,

693
00:57:57,369 --> 00:58:00,806
"Your mum wants me to tell you
there's no such thing as Bagman."

694
00:58:03,411 --> 00:58:04,975
But I'm afraid I can't do that.

695
00:58:09,183 --> 00:58:10,211
What I can do...

696
00:58:11,852 --> 00:58:14,754
is tell you a secret he
don't want you to know.

697
00:58:16,992 --> 00:58:18,887
Truth is,

698
00:58:18,888 --> 00:58:22,524
no matter how big, or
fast, or sneaky he is,

699
00:58:22,525 --> 00:58:23,994
he has weaknesses as well.

700
00:58:25,601 --> 00:58:28,504
Escape his grasp long
enough, he'll rot away.

701
00:58:30,068 --> 00:58:33,234
And he cannot lay a single,
skinny finger on you.

702
00:58:34,439 --> 00:58:35,544
Not as long...

703
00:58:37,410 --> 00:58:38,410
as you have this.

704
00:58:43,716 --> 00:58:45,279
You see, every
kid's got something

705
00:58:45,280 --> 00:58:48,018
that means more to them than
anything else in the world.

706
00:58:49,852 --> 00:58:51,087
Something they love so much,

707
00:58:53,090 --> 00:58:55,597
it literally becomes a
piece of who they are.

708
00:58:56,561 --> 00:58:57,896
And believe you me,

709
00:58:58,695 --> 00:59:00,030
a child's love...

710
00:59:01,599 --> 00:59:03,568
can be a magical thing.

711
00:59:03,569 --> 00:59:05,805
It can turn even the
humblest object...

712
00:59:07,571 --> 00:59:08,742
into a totem...

713
00:59:09,507 --> 00:59:10,942
of great power.

714
00:59:15,045 --> 00:59:17,348
Now you keep this
close to your heart,

715
00:59:17,349 --> 00:59:19,280
and he cannot touch you.

716
00:59:24,258 --> 00:59:25,687
But lose it,

717
00:59:25,688 --> 00:59:28,058
or even worse, throw it away...

718
00:59:38,835 --> 00:59:39,839
So, you keep ahold of it.

719
00:59:41,275 --> 00:59:42,275
No matter what.

720
00:59:47,943 --> 00:59:50,212
And now you're concerned...

721
00:59:51,287 --> 00:59:52,367
that Fute has gone missing.

722
00:59:54,252 --> 00:59:56,625
If the one thing that can
supposedly protect Jake...

723
00:59:58,128 --> 00:59:59,128
from you-know-who...

724
01:00:00,661 --> 01:00:02,061
is the thing that
he loves the most?

725
01:00:03,590 --> 01:00:04,930
Honestly?

726
01:00:09,167 --> 01:00:11,700
Well, what I wanna do
right now is go back home

727
01:00:11,701 --> 01:00:13,103
and dig through the trash again.

728
01:00:15,138 --> 01:00:16,907
But if we go down
that thought track,

729
01:00:16,908 --> 01:00:18,908
I'm not sure we'll make it
to the other side, so...

730
01:00:25,048 --> 01:00:26,853
Did Barbara help
when you were eight?

731
01:00:28,185 --> 01:00:29,955
Wouldn't have made it
to nine without her.

732
01:00:31,559 --> 01:00:32,892
So, we have to trust her now.

733
01:00:51,878 --> 01:00:54,481
No, I do not miss you at all.

734
01:00:54,482 --> 01:00:56,349
<i>What?</i> ANNA: Mmm-mmm.

735
01:00:56,350 --> 01:00:58,780
I have a real hot date tonight.

736
01:00:58,781 --> 01:01:00,916
<i>- Oh, yeah?</i>
- Three feet tall,

737
01:01:00,917 --> 01:01:03,585
talks gibberish and
craps his own pants.

738
01:01:03,586 --> 01:01:05,820
It is so, so sexy.

739
01:01:05,821 --> 01:01:07,190
<i>Stop it.</i>

740
01:01:08,363 --> 01:01:10,164
Okay, babe, um...

741
01:01:10,165 --> 01:01:11,426
We'll see you tomorrow.

742
01:01:11,427 --> 01:01:12,493
<i>Yeah.</i>

743
01:01:12,494 --> 01:01:14,535
Yeah.

744
01:01:14,536 --> 01:01:19,000
And why don't you make
me something sweet?

745
01:01:19,001 --> 01:01:21,535
<i>Something sweet?
What do you mean?</i>

746
01:01:22,838 --> 01:01:24,005
<i>I don't know what you mean.</i>

747
01:01:24,006 --> 01:01:26,341
You know exactly what
I'm talking about.

748
01:01:28,581 --> 01:01:30,984
Okay. Okay, babe.

749
01:01:30,985 --> 01:01:32,083
Yeah. Bye.

750
01:02:52,763 --> 01:02:53,827
<i>Hey.</i>

751
01:02:53,828 --> 01:02:55,361
- Angelo.
<i>- Yeah?</i>

752
01:02:55,362 --> 01:02:58,570
Is there something weird
happening on this floor?

753
01:02:58,571 --> 01:03:00,701
<i>Uh, what do you mean, "weird"?</i>

754
01:03:00,702 --> 01:03:02,037
I don't know.

755
01:03:02,038 --> 01:03:04,271
I'm hearing a voice
on a baby monitor.

756
01:03:04,272 --> 01:03:06,709
<i>Everything's clear
on my security cams.</i>

757
01:03:06,710 --> 01:03:07,774
<i>You want me to come up?</i>

758
01:03:07,775 --> 01:03:09,147
No, no. Um...

759
01:03:09,880 --> 01:03:11,384
I'm sure it's nothing.

760
01:03:11,385 --> 01:03:13,416
<i>Okay. Take it easy.</i>

761
01:03:13,417 --> 01:03:14,449
Yeah.

762
01:03:25,669 --> 01:03:27,869
Angelo, has there
been a power surge?

763
01:03:29,867 --> 01:03:31,499
Angelo, are you there?

764
01:03:36,544 --> 01:03:37,544
Come on.

765
01:03:39,709 --> 01:03:40,816
Shit.

766
01:04:20,921 --> 01:04:23,050
I don't know what
you want from me.

767
01:04:23,051 --> 01:04:25,289
But the cops are on their way!

768
01:04:30,533 --> 01:04:32,032
Did I mention I have a gun?

769
01:04:37,234 --> 01:04:39,402
Don't play with
me, motherfucker!

770
01:04:57,160 --> 01:04:58,160
Sarah!

771
01:04:59,022 --> 01:05:00,995
Sarah, call the police!

772
01:06:28,716 --> 01:06:29,716
Stay back.

773
01:06:30,849 --> 01:06:31,849
Karina.

774
01:06:33,051 --> 01:06:35,080
Anna? Anna, are you okay?

775
01:06:35,081 --> 01:06:36,486
Are you okay?

776
01:06:37,988 --> 01:06:38,820
What happened?

777
01:06:38,821 --> 01:06:40,424
Where's Jakie?

778
01:06:42,094 --> 01:06:43,860
We got him. He's okay.

779
01:06:43,861 --> 01:06:45,693
Hey, buddy. Hey. Hey.

780
01:06:46,700 --> 01:06:47,700
There you go.

781
01:06:49,033 --> 01:06:50,564
It's okay. Thank you.

782
01:06:50,565 --> 01:06:53,533
We've got nothing
on the CCTV camera.

783
01:06:53,534 --> 01:06:56,077
It was knocked out when
the power went down.

784
01:06:57,108 --> 01:06:58,673
Thank God for the doorman.

785
01:07:00,411 --> 01:07:03,011
Once the camera on
Anna's floor went dark,

786
01:07:03,012 --> 01:07:04,514
he headed straight up.

787
01:07:05,888 --> 01:07:08,019
He must have scared the guy off.

788
01:07:08,020 --> 01:07:09,585
- Did Angelo get a look at him?
- No.

789
01:07:10,921 --> 01:07:12,385
But, Pat,

790
01:07:12,386 --> 01:07:14,188
apparently there
are similarities

791
01:07:14,189 --> 01:07:16,295
to a case from four years ago.

792
01:07:18,397 --> 01:07:21,066
A girl named Emily
Greenberg went missing.

793
01:07:21,067 --> 01:07:24,168
Her dad suffered similar
symptoms to Anna's,

794
01:07:24,169 --> 01:07:28,601
temporary paralysis
and loss of speech.

795
01:07:28,602 --> 01:07:32,744
And these strange
abrasions on his face.

796
01:07:32,745 --> 01:07:34,082
He said he couldn't move.

797
01:07:34,914 --> 01:07:36,081
He had to lie there

798
01:07:36,082 --> 01:07:37,445
and watch this lunatic
stuff his daughter

799
01:07:37,446 --> 01:07:40,319
